                                                       // Tapping on the desired bookmark displays the appropriate tab.\n\nIn total there 
                                                       // are 4 tabs: settings, search, saved list and the memory editor.\n\t* In the upper 
                                                       // right corner of the interface is the closing button. Press it and the interface 
                                                       // will be hidden, and a floating icon will appear on the screen.\n\t* At the bottom 
                                                       // of the screen there is a status bar and the eye icon. If you press and hold on the 
                                                       // eye icon, the interface becomes transparent, as long as you do not release your 
                                                       // finger.\n\t* The rest of the contents on the screen depends on which tab you\'re 
                                                       // on.\n\nOn each tab, except for the settings tab, there is a menu button, which contains 
                                                       // a variety of possible actions. In it you will find the main actions for this tab.\n\nSettings 
                                                       // tab contains a variety of settings, help, and information about the application, 
