    public static final int help_faq_4_a = 0x7F0701C1;  // string:help_faq_4_a "You must take a simple program that is guaranteed to have no 
                                                        // protection and try it. I prefer to use \"Hill Climb Racing\". The game is simple, 
                                                        // uncomplicated and does not contain any defenses. You can check the hacking of money 
                                                        // as a direct search by number, and fuzzy search for change.\nIf hacking on this simple 
                                                        // game works, then it\'s in that X game that you tried to hack. If not, then the problem 
                                                        // is in __app_name__.\nThere is even an easier option: \"Tap Counter\". Install it. 
                                                        // Run. Try to crack the number of tapes displayed on the screen. It should be very 
                                                        // easy. If not, then the problem is in __app_name__ or its settings.\nTry another 
                                                        // version of __app_name__, try to search for a description of the error received on 
                                                        // the forum in the relevant topic or on the Internet. In extreme cases, you can ask 
