                                                                     // firmware or change the device.\n\t5. Remove __app_name__ from the system.\n\t6. 
                                                                     // Work with __app_name__ from virtual space. \n\nFor avoid detect during the search:\n\tSelect 
                                                                     // items 2, 3 and 4 in \"__hide_from_game__\" setting. \n\nA typical solution (requires 
                                                                     // root, without root you won’t succeed):\n\t1. Use root from virtual space. Read the 
                                                                     // help for the setting \"__vspace_root__\".\n\t2. Use items 2, 3 and 4 in the \"__hide_from_game__\" 
                                                                     // setting.\n    "
    public static final int help_games_protection_title = 0x7F07026E;  // string:help_games_protection_title "How to get around protection in games"
    public static final int help_group_search = 0x7F070127;  // string:help_group_search "* Group search:\n\t1. Switch to __app_name__ from a game.\n\t2. 
                                                             // Tap the \"__search_known_value__\" button in the \"__search__\" tab.\n\t3. Input 
                                                             // search request for group search.\n\t\tFormat: value 1 __semicolon__ value 2 __semicolon__ 
                                                             // ... __semicolon__ value N __colon__ group size\n\t\t2-__max_group__ values can be 
                                                             // searched at the same time. The default group size is 512. The group size must be 
                                                             // between 2 and 65536.\n\t\tFor example, if you want to search 195 and 6543, you should 
                                                             // input:\n\t\t\t195 __semicolon__ 6543\n\t\tOf course you can specify the group size 
                                                             // (300):\n\t\t\t195 __semicolon__ 6543 __colon__ 300\n\t\tAlso, you can set one or 
                                                             // more data types:\n\t\t\t195__type_dword_short__ __semicolon__ 6543\n\t\tThis means 
                                                             // you want to search a __type_dword__ value that is 195 and an __type_auto__ value 
                                                             // that is 6543.\n\t\tPossible data types are the same as they are in search: \n\t\t\t__type_byte_short__ 
                                                             // - __type_byte__\n\t\t\t__type_word_short__ - __type_word__\n\t\t\t__type_dword_short__ 
                                                             // - __type_dword__\n\t\t\t__type_xor_short__ - __type_xor__\n\t\t\t__type_qword_short__ 
                                                             // - __type_qword__\n\t\t\t__type_float_short__ - __type_float__\n\t\t\t__type_double_short__ 
                                                             // - __type_double__\n\t\t\t__type_auto_short__ - __type_auto__\n\t\tAlso you can write 
                                                             // the number in hex (little-endian) notation:\n\t\t\t__hex_example____hex__ __semicolon__ 
                                                             // 6543\n\t\tor in reverse hex (big-endian) notation:\n\t\t\t__hex_example____rhex__ 
                                                             // __semicolon__ 6543\n\t\tTo input additional symbols, use the \"__btn_hex__\" button 
                                                             // on internal keyboard.\n\t4. Select the suitable data type, or choose \"__type_auto__\" 
                                                             // (if you are not sure) to use as default. Other options do not matter for this type 
                                                             // of search. Click \"__search__\".\n\t5. When finished searching, search result will 
                                                             // be displayed in the list.\n\t6. Back to the game. After the value has changed, switch 
                                                             // to __app_name__ again.\n\t7. Repeat group search with appropriate changes.\n\t8. 
                                                             // If there are too many results, repeat steps 6 and 7.\n\t9. If few results are left, 
                                                             // you can try to modify, store or freeze the value.\n\n\tIf you want respect order 
                                                             // of values then specify __colon__ twice.\n\tWithout group size:\n\t\t195 __semicolon__ 
                                                             // 6543 __colon____colon__\n\tWith group size:\n\t\t195 __semicolon__ 6543 __colon____colon__ 
                                                             // 300\n\n\tYou can search in the range of values:\n\t\t190__tilde__210 __semicolon__ 
                                                             // 6543\n\tAlso you can search outside the range of values:\n\t\t10__tilde____tilde__4000 
                                                             // __semicolon__ 6543\n    "
