    public static final int help_text_search = 0x7F07031E;  // string:help_text_search "\nTo search for text, you must specify modifiers in the 
                                                            // usual search dialog.\n\nThe most commonly used encodings are __utf8__ and __utf16le__.\nTypically, 
                                                            // __utf16le__ is used in __java__, and __utf8__ is used in __c__.\n\n\t__utf16le__ 
                                                            // is a two-byte encoding. Each character is always encoded in two bytes, so it is 
                                                            // represented via __type_word__.\n\t__utf8__ - encoding with variable byte size per 
                                                            // character. Represented via __type_byte__.\n\t__hex_input__ and its variants are 
                                                            // always represented via __type_byte__.\n\nThe game can use any of the encodings.\nIf 
                                                            // you need a specific set of bytes - use the __hex_input__ mode.\n\nAvailable prefixes:\n__text_prefixes__\n\nFor 
                                                            // \"__hex_mixed__\" mode, you can specify __utf8__ text between __apos__ characters 
                                                            // and __utf16le__ text between __quot__ characters.\n\nFor example:\n__text_examples__\n\nThe 
                                                            // prefix character must be the first character in the search text.\n\nThe result of 
                                                            // the search will be a __type_byte__ sequence, or a __type_word__ sequence, for the 
                                                            // case of __utf16le__.\n\nThe results can be changed - select all and click \"__edit_selected__\".\n\nIn 
                                                            // the value field, enter the new value, in the same format as for the search string.\n\nYou 
                                                            // can use the fill buttons. Click \"__more__\" if they are not visible.\n\nThe value 
                                                            // will be set for each group of continuously following items.\nIf there is a gap between 
                                                            // the elements, it will be a new group.\n\nIf you specify more bytes than needed, 
                                                            // then only a part of them will be used.\nIf you specify less than needed, then the 
                                                            // rest of the group will be filled with zero bytes.\n\nWhen replacing text, try to 
                                                            // specify text with the same number of bytes as the original to avoid problems.\n 
                                                            //    "
    public static final int help_typical_usage = 0x7F070129;  // string:help_typical_usage "* Typical usage algorithms:\n\n1) The value is not encrypted 
                                                              // and known.\n\tA typical case would be for money, stars, coins, resources, etc.\n\n\tUse 
                                                              // exact search. \n\n2) The value is unknown and/or encrypted.\n\tA typical case of 
                                                              // an unknown value - any scale/bar. For example health, mana, nitro, etc. The changes 
                                                              // are seen, but no numerical values are visible.\n\tA typical case for encrypted values 
                                                              // would be money, stars, coins, etc., but when searching with 1 algorithm does not 
                                                              // find anything, or change of found values does not lead to numbers changing in the 
                                                              // game.\n\n\tUse fuzzy search.\n\n\n3) The value is encrypted (__mode_hacking__).\n\tA 
                                                              // typical case for encrypted values would be money, stars, coins, etc., but when searching 
                                                              // with 1 algorithm does not find anything, or change of found values does not lead 
                                                              // to numbers changing in the game.\n\n\tUse exact search, but always select the checkbox 
                                                              // \"__mode_hacking__\". \n\tFound results may have strange values due to encryption.\n\nAlgorithm 
                                                              // 3 is much faster than 2, but it may not work for all games.\n\n4) The value is not 
                                                              // encrypted, known and placed near other known values.\n\tA typical case would be 
                                                              // for price in store, hero stats, etc.\n\n\tUse group search for all numbers in one 
                                                              // time. \n    "
    public static final int help_typical_usage_title = 0x7F070131;  // string:help_typical_usage_title "Typical usage algorithms"
    public static final int help_unaligned = 0x7F07030B;  // string:help_unaligned "In some applications, (for example, such as console emulators), 
                                                          // the value in memory may not respect alignment, or be presented in big-endian byte 
                                                          // order.\n\nSuch value can not be found through a normal search.\n\nTo find them - 
